town. He even lent money to the young John Brown for an Ohio farm before Brown's speculation collapsed in the Panic of 1837.","number":4}],"slug":"frederick-wadsworth-1786"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM003","name":"Ancient Burying Ground","city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","gps":{"latitude":41.7627,"longitude":-72.6743},"founded":1640,"visitable":true,"notes":"Adjacent to Center Church. Earliest surviving identifiable gravestone dates to 1648. Resting place of many Hartford founders including Rev. Thomas Hooker (exact location unknown).","hooker_connections":["H00001","H00033","H00102","H00110","H00115","H00362","I00053","T00011","T00383","T00384","T00385","T00386","T00387","T00388","X00067","X00110","X00123","X00418","X01014","X02128","X02129","X00049","H00028","I00056","X02130","X00066","H00032","H00340","X00083","X00050","X01998","TD0058","T00071","X01763","U00017","U00022","T00045","X03384"]},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}